Maximum Score from Binary Array
🧩 Problem

Given a binary array A of even length N, you must perform N/2 operations:

Choose an index i such that 1 ≤ i < size of A
Add |A[i] - A[i+1]| to score
Remove both elements from the array

Return the maximum possible score.

💡 Approach
🔍 Key Idea
|A[i] - A[i+1]| = 1 if elements are different
|A[i] - A[i+1]| = 0 if elements are same

👉 So, we need to maximize the number of (0,1) or (1,0) pairs

🧠 Observation

Each valid pair consumes:

one 0
one 1

Thus, the maximum number of such pairs is:

min(count of 0s, count of 1s)
✅ Algorithm
Count number of 0s and 1s in the array
Return min(zeros, ones)
🚀 Java Implementation
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();

        while (t-- > 0) {
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            int zeros = 0, ones = 0;

            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                int x = sc.nextInt();
                if (x == 0) zeros++;
                else ones++;
            }

            System.out.println(Math.min(zeros, ones));
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}
⏱ Complexity
Time: O(N) per test case
Space: O(1)
📊 Example
Input:
1
4
1 1 0 0

Output:
2
